==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hunts-up
<hw>Hunt's"-up`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tune played on
the horn very early in the morning to call out the hunters; hence, any
arousing sound or call.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Time plays the <qex>hunt's-up</qex> to thy sleepy head.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurden</ent>⟦br⟧
